{
  "text": "In an SSC model for the flares, the NIR photons are produced by a momentarily accelerated population of electrons radiating in the NIR band via a synchrotron process. In the following we will use the simple parametrization of [CITATION_1] in which a spherical homogeneous source of synchrotron radiation with a radius R and a volumic electron density n e , pervaded by a magnetic field B, has a power-law energy distribution:",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "18924157"
